"dokja—yah can we not fight anymore please? can we not fight anymo…
To end this, the whole of Kim Dokja's Company totally got semicolon tattoos when Kim Dokja woke up after the epilogue.

But I would love to see more exploration of Kim Dokja's mental illness and past and present of self harming tendencies.

This fandom is so wonderful that I know any and all of you would be able to do it justice,

Maybe I'm just jaded by my other fandom, where they make jokes about therapists being terrible and how the characters will never recover from their trauma.

I guess I just don't want the ORV fandom to be like that, and I know you guys usually aren't.

Because a big theme with ORV is healing and learning that you are allowed to be loved. It delves so deeply into understanding and accepting yourself, which is something so many people with mental illness struggle to do.
Like humor about them needing therapy and being traumatized is all well and good, but I think that if we don't also discuss the topic seriously, we lose a lot to be learned from ORV.

This is coming from someone who has experienced the same things, so maybe I'm projecting. Or maybe I can see him a bit clearer because of that.

I just wish there was more discussion of his and the other characters' mental health. In a non joking manner.

There are just so many traits that are obvious when you pay attention. But that's for another rant.

What I want to get across is that Kim Dokja is one of the most human depictions of a mentally ill and suicidal person that I have ever witnessed.

He is self-sacrificial to the point of suicidality and his self worth is nonexistent. He treats himself far different from how he treats other people. 

From my point of view, he definitely has at least C-PTSD and ADHD.

First of all, it would be incredibly difficult to go through all the things KDJ has without developing unhealthy coping mechanisms and mental illnesses, and you can see from his behaviors that he has developed them.

Kim Dokja's mental health is such an integral part of ORV that I wish was discussed more. 

Not to armchair diagnose a fictional character, but his behaviors are caught in stunning clarity when you look at them through the lens of mental illness.

The day their relationship really changes is the day Yoo Joonghyuk sings to Kim Dokja. It was after a scenario that forces KDJ to suffer through his worst memories.

He wakes up to YJH cradling him and singing in a husky, unused voice. So soft only KDJ and YJH can hear.

One day, when Kim Dokja has been having a rough week and the Company was just drudging through, YJH forces something into KDJ's hand.

It's a kalimba. Something KDJ had mentioned wanting once, weeks ago.

KDJ does not tear up, but he does work hard to learn so he can play for YJH

Kim Dokja sings to Yoo Joonghyuk a lot after that. He excuses it by saying that he gets a lot of coins from the constellations when he sings, anyways, but they both know its not just that.

Because Kim Dokja sings Yoo Joonghyuk love songs.

YJH asks him to sing. At first, KDJ is reticent because he never thought YJH cared about music.

Still, he sings. And as he does, Yoo Joonghyuk gets a vulnerable look on his face that Kim Dokja is absolutely sure no one has ever seen before.

Yoo Joonghyuk is struck. He's never heard a voice that resonated with him like that. He usually only ever liked video game music, but this was something more.

After that, he hunts down KDJ when he is singing enough times that Kim Dokja just asks him what his problem is.

When Yoo Joonghyuk really joins them, Kim Dokja purposefully sings badly just to piss him off. So, for a while, YJH simply thinks KDJ is a terrible singer.

Until Lee Jihye has a panic attack and Kim Dokja sings one of her favorite songs to calm her down.

Jung Heewon forces him into belting pop songs with her. Lee Hyunsung suggests he sing to raise the Company's mood.

But Lee Gilyoung's requests are the ones that KDJ always fulfills.

The Company is shocked. They never expected such a beautiful voice to come from a man like Kim Dokja, but from then on they try all the ways to hear it again.

Yoo Sangah asks him to sing songs she is beginning to forget.

The first time he sings among his company is when Lee Gilyoung is having a nightmare and no one has any idea of how to soothe him.

KDJ holds the kids hand and softly sings a lullaby he had almost forgotten.

Everyone stares. But it works.

So when everything goes down, he agonizes over all the lost music and how he only has the songs he's downloaded on his phone to keep him sane.

He goes off on his own, even when it's dangerous, because he just needs to sing. It is his melody in the cacophony of the game.

Even when he was bullied for it, even as he grew, he just couldn't give up his love of music. 

He found a job that specifically wouldn't mind him listening to music while he worked. He bought a record player just for its sound. Its the only object he has that he truly loves.

OKAY BUT a Kim Dokja who can sing! Who's only respites from the hell that was his life was Ways of Survival and music! 

A Kim Dokja who made playlists for every mood and fantasy he had. Who would find the most secluded places just so he could sing and hear the echo singing back
